This is untested but compiles. If it's workable I think it would be a better direction to go in, both to keep blockstorage code simpler, but also to provide better support for buffered reads and writes in the stream API in case there are other parts of code that could benefit from them.

I am also ok with with current approach and happy to review if there are issues with this or it's just not the direction we want to go.

@maflcko / @ryanofsky, this implementation seems to fail in the same weird way as https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/actions/runs/12918565902/job/36027337187?pr=31539 - with 100% tests passing.
The last PR indicates it's the batch writing part - could it be an OOM because the sanitizer overhead in `DataStream#resize(1 << 20)`?
`WriteBlockBench` indicates that even a buffer size of `1 << 16` is half the speed (Linux/GCC speed is the same) - but I'll try it, let's see if it passes CI at least.

